INSERT INTO items VALUES('https://laconservancy.tumblr.com/post/667501561362137088','The West L.A. Civic Center and L.A.&rsquo;s Historic Preservation Problem','<div class="npf_row"><figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="2048" data-orig-width="3072"><img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s640x960/debc7478f3996152b7600e84d4bc127a8eb9db79.jpg" data-orig-height="2048" data-orig-width="3072" srcset="https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s75x75_c1/b173450051daf33ad8b90c32b6dc839ecfbedb76.jpg 75w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s100x200/08c00d8a36a018d33b63f7c453db834ab1390728.jpg 100w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s250x400/5fd0e4429792c1257797ea0d4339de5550aec9e3.jpg 250w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s400x600/39f4bdac02d5739b2dbfd0f0624b6a6a499ee6e3.jpg 400w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s500x750/36f66893febfd289b7869323fb0c73bda3d9ec9e.jpg 500w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s540x810/6cedfc2fe8b01212edd9443271df04b01d1912dc.jpg 540w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s640x960/debc7478f3996152b7600e84d4bc127a8eb9db79.jpg 640w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s1280x1920/c6406f0fd58015888a5d8f665fa8b88e32bd0fc8.jpg 1280w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/495e2b294eb16b04a2a80d13c2d235e5/7d56218b522cd5d1-56/s2048x3072/6bbd923d5b20b578086633cb55bebfaf9f65343b.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"/></figure></div><p>Think you know what’s up with the proposed redevelopment of the West L.A. Civic Center? The November 9th, 2021 West L.A. Commons community meeting shed some light and details on the project but few on preservation, much like the project itself.</p><p>Here’s the scoop:</p><!-- more --><p>Built between 1957-1965 to meet growing demand for government services, the West L.A. Civic Center is significant for its Modernist architecture and role in expanded government services following WWII. More recently, it’s become hallowed ground for L.A.’s skateboarding scene, attracting skaters worldwide with its stairs and ledges. In January 2021, the County and City selected Abode Communities and AvalonBay Communities to redevelop the site.</p><p>As currently planned, the 1960 Courthouse, 1961 branch City Hall, 1962 Community Center (Senior Center), and 1965 Amphitheatre are to be demolished.</p><p>(Only the 1956 library will stay&ndash;for now&ndash;and is not a part of this project scope.)</p><p><b><i>This means an eligible historic district marking an important part of West L.A.’s growth will be erased.</i></b></p><div class="npf_row"><figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="1116" data-orig-width="2162"><img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s640x960/c3b0fd9f4ee68d0686aae3aae649d720b8d3f415.png" data-orig-height="1116" data-orig-width="2162" srcset="https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s75x75_c1/bcf93f8913366df74319f362178f4057bf6013f0.png 75w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s100x200/de42bf391aff8dbaf58b378533c4ec98fd54fb20.png 100w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s250x400/c6d1c1bfdf86ef362f3b76bfb1e9ee601dbf9b85.png 250w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s400x600/5661752f988e64d264741662ab6e9ae92c7cd838.png 400w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s500x750/6658c292823af57d5be3b77c8ca30cbe5d814eec.png 500w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s540x810/78b2233f2b045fd70c4ba70fb49ba711bafca087.png 540w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s640x960/c3b0fd9f4ee68d0686aae3aae649d720b8d3f415.png 640w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s1280x1920/fdd6914c02b61e1f5c7a5cb98a8c3fb3969ea2a4.png 1280w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/a85d3207a7dfd2b124a112a4e52f75a8/7d56218b522cd5d1-cc/s2048x3072/4d42ef1d213ec27cabe2a087171a846e391451d2.png 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"/></figure></div><p>Two facades of the branch City Hall were planned to be kept (which is not preservation) yet that is now being reconsidered, citing soil conditions. The same goes for the now-doomed Googie style Amphitheatre, despite being marked for preservation in the proposal that was selected by the City and County.</p><p>As a public-private venture between the City, County and the developer (AvalonBay and Abode Communities), preservation was supposed to be a priority, at least it was in the official Request for Proposals (RFP) process, stated as one of ten key aspects to be addressed.</p><p><i>So … what is happening here?</i></p><p>Preservation through adaptive reuse is readily achievable in this project, and can complement the proposed new mixed income housing. New buildings of the same footprint are to replace the branch City Hall and Courthouse. The existing Amphitheatre can be repurposed and kept.</p><p>It is easier to demolish everything and build subterranean parking over the entire site than build around the historic buildings. Yet easy does not equal better. Until someone in leadership steps forward and presses for an alternative that successfully marries the old with the new, this development team will continue to seek the easy way out. As a familiar pattern that keeps repeating itself across this city, L.A. can do and deserves better.</p><p>Please join the L.A. Conservancy in pressing City Councilmember Mike Bonin and County Supervisor Sheila Kuehl for another alternative! Email them at: councilmember.bonin@lacity.org and sheila<a class="tumblelog" href="https://tmblr.co/Moegh9HgI0-jorxNRNi2Nkw" target="_blank">@bos</a>.lacounty.gov. Be sure to cc afine<a class="tumblelog" href="https://tmblr.co/MfiBgGJRvlu7TnLPToOIIQA" target="_blank">@laconservancy</a>.org so that we can track!</p><div class="npf_row"><figure class="tmblr-full" data-orig-height="3024" data-orig-width="4032"><img src="https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s640x960/0a01cbf06e04a7ec5e9c2a14e05b01b0bf9ef7d4.jpg" data-orig-height="3024" data-orig-width="4032" srcset="https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s75x75_c1/4181a73de0682ef22158f4c244ef40c1ca14e2b0.jpg 75w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s100x200/209b574eb44d0cd3c71d61da199f8738deadc7e3.jpg 100w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s250x400/ea3c254e78f8ff7b832f74aa2017635aca3034ef.jpg 250w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s400x600/44657770cf30711de080b171c9452c0fdfeca07c.jpg 400w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s500x750/098598d0e6a5e8a506d71111ed6be509236d28b6.jpg 500w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s540x810/801f69dd6ecd99c445925a3e86ed50eafa607a91.jpg 540w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s640x960/0a01cbf06e04a7ec5e9c2a14e05b01b0bf9ef7d4.jpg 640w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s1280x1920/e0d8e9e4e98f31e50d76fa02bf05860304be312d.jpg 1280w, https://64.media.tumblr.com/38ab0bfbfadec3c8df4f81808ce9faf5/7d56218b522cd5d1-47/s2048x3072/aa55ff82de93369923ce370dd16c5ac961e1dd5e.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"/></figure><figure class="tmblr-f